form2:
Step 1 of 5:
•	What is a ‚sustainability transformation‘?
•	Formulation of 17 appears a bit vague to me
•	I am not entirely sure what is meant by (31)
•	(4) Synergies for what?
•	(24) also not sure what is meant here
•	(32) ‘while redistributing access’: access to what remains open to me
•	(1) ‘Maximise the efficient’: is this formulation correct in economic terms?
•	(26) For me the direction of the ‘advance’ remains unclear: advance to what?
•	I do not really know what a bio-economy is
•	(33) appears to me to be a bit more academic than the rest
•	(11) I am not so sure what I have to assess here
•	(18) I do not have an immediately imagination what this capacity would be
Steps 2 of 5:
•	It would be nice to have a headline here that reminds me against what backdrop I have to state my (dis-)agreement
Steps 5 of 5:
“What kind of approach do you mainly work with in your job?” – I think none. Can I tick that?
I do not have a precise understand of bio-economy and circular-economy. Here I am a bit guessing would one could mean.
dur1: (s5) I personally do not want to live in a world (and inherit it to my children) that is carbon neural etc. but lost the variety of natural live. For me there is a moral imperative to protect nature.
dur2: (s28) I fear that an increase of the economic production comes most likely at the cost of nature degradation. I believe that in industrialized countries, growth does not increase wellbeing but might increase inequalities.
